WEBVTT

00:03.903 --> 00:07.270
<i>##[Chorus Singing]</i>

00:07.374 --> 00:09.274
[Tires Screeching]

00:10.443 --> 00:12.343
D'oh!
[Screams]

00:14.000 --> 00:20.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:26.393 --> 00:27.917
<i>##[Theme Song]</i>

00:31.264 --> 00:33.562
Hmm.

00:34.667 --> 00:37.966
- I want a job.
- You've got it.

00:38.071 --> 00:40.096
- <i>[Yelling]</i>
- <i>[Flames Lapping]</i>

00:40.206 --> 00:43.369
- <i>Ooh, ooh. Ow!</i>
- [Blowing]

00:43.476 --> 00:45.910
[Whimpers]

00:46.012 --> 00:47.809
I quit.

00:47.914 --> 00:50.109
- <i>[Screams]</i>
- <i>[Flames Lapping]</i>

00:53.653 --> 00:56.417
[Scratchy]
No. No. No!

00:56.523 --> 00:59.424
[Laughing]

00:59.526 --> 01:03.394
Man, you'd think the quality
would dip after 5,500 shows.

01:03.496 --> 01:05.396
But-
[Laughs]

01:05.498 --> 01:07.557
Well, the F.C.C.
isn't laughing.

01:07.667 --> 01:10.431
They don't believe kids are learning anything
from Itchy and Scratchy.

01:10.537 --> 01:13.267
Aw, please.
What don't they learn?

01:13.373 --> 01:16.137
Don't trust mice.
Cats are made of glass.

01:16.242 --> 01:18.369
Our license renewal
is on the bubble.

01:18.478 --> 01:20.844
We need educational
programming fast.

01:20.947 --> 01:24.747
What about that <i>Mattel and Mars Bar</i>
<i>Quick Energy Chocobot Hour?</i>

01:24.851 --> 01:27.718
<i>That's barely legal as it is.</i>
<i>Here's what I was thinking.</i>

01:27.821 --> 01:30.756
A newscast for kids by kids.

01:30.857 --> 01:33.291
Well, you're not taking
any time out of my show.

01:33.393 --> 01:36.021
It's jammed up as it is.
There's the monologue...

01:36.129 --> 01:38.757
those idiot puppets,
Krusty's nap time...

01:38.865 --> 01:42.323
the second monologue,
Paul Harvey, Senor Pepino-

01:42.435 --> 01:45.700
I tell ya, it's the tightest three hours
and 10 minutes on TV.

01:45.805 --> 01:48.330
- We're cutting 10 minutes from your show.
- Well, I guess...

01:48.441 --> 01:50.807
we could trim the hobo parade
to a lean 20.

01:53.379 --> 01:55.609
Ach. She's a bonny pile.

01:55.715 --> 01:58.479
Now for a wee nip and a wee nap.

02:01.020 --> 02:03.045
[Chains Squeaking]

02:03.156 --> 02:05.590
- Ready, Milhouse?
- Ready.

02:05.692 --> 02:07.626
[Grunts]

02:07.727 --> 02:09.661
[Girls Shriek]

02:10.864 --> 02:12.889
- Whoa!
- [All] Whoa!

02:13.766 --> 02:15.666
[Quick Grunts]

02:15.768 --> 02:17.759
You owe me a quarter.
I didn't crack my skull.

02:17.871 --> 02:19.998
- Rats.
- [Yells]

02:20.106 --> 02:23.075
- [Grunts]
- Ach! Me pile!

02:23.176 --> 02:25.303
It's been raped of its "bonny-ness."

02:25.411 --> 02:27.572
- [Groans]
- Hi, Willie.

02:27.680 --> 02:30.911
- [Gasps] My board!
- It's Willie's board now.

02:31.017 --> 02:33.485
And she'll make
a fine piece of kindlir.

02:36.789 --> 02:40.054
- <i>[Knocking]</i>
- Sorry. Willie can't hear ya.

02:40.160 --> 02:42.151
## [Bagpipes]

02:42.262 --> 02:44.253
## [More Bagpipes]

02:44.364 --> 02:46.491
## [Bagpipes]

02:49.435 --> 02:51.665
<i>Hmm.</i>

02:51.771 --> 02:53.762
[Liquid Sloshing]

02:57.644 --> 02:59.942
- It's pure.
- Hmm.

03:03.349 --> 03:05.647
I really didn't want it
to come to this.

03:06.886 --> 03:10.253
- ## [Whistling]
- [Snoring]

03:11.624 --> 03:15.116
Lisa, Channel 6 is launching
a childrers news program...

03:15.228 --> 03:18.664
and they've asked me to select
an outstanding student to be anchorchild.

03:18.765 --> 03:20.665
[Gasps]
Oh, my gosh!

03:20.767 --> 03:23.201
Today's top story- Little girl on cloud nine
as dream comes true.

03:23.303 --> 03:26.500
Lisa, I've selected you
to be that child anchor.

03:26.606 --> 03:28.597
I know. I already jumped
to that conclusion.

03:28.708 --> 03:31.370
Hmm. All right.
If you're so smart...

03:31.477 --> 03:33.775
tell me who I selected
to be lunchroom monitor.

03:33.880 --> 03:37.281
- Me?
- Take your sash and go.

03:40.019 --> 03:42.954
This isn't right.
This isn't right at all.

03:43.056 --> 03:44.990
Ugh. Aw.

03:45.091 --> 03:48.652
[Grunts]
I'll have to eat my way out.

03:48.761 --> 03:52.026
[Chomping]

03:52.131 --> 03:54.895
Agh!
It's terrible.

03:55.902 --> 03:58.302
<i>[Explosion]</i>

03:58.404 --> 04:00.372
<i>[Birds Chirping]</i>

04:03.876 --> 04:06.470
My shack!
My beautiful shack!

04:06.579 --> 04:09.173
Oh, and I just got it
the way I like it.

04:09.282 --> 04:11.375
[Laughs]

04:12.919 --> 04:14.853
You did this, Bart Simpson!

04:14.954 --> 04:16.853
The man knows quality work.

04:16.956 --> 04:18.856
This time you're in for it, Bart.

04:18.958 --> 04:20.858
[Scoffs]
Huh! What's he gonna do?

04:20.959 --> 04:23.861
- I'll kill ya!
- [Chokes]

04:23.963 --> 04:26.158
[Nurse] All right.
Back on the stretcher.

04:27.900 --> 04:30.630
And I'll be able to tackle
all the hard-hitting childrers news...

04:30.737 --> 04:32.898
the grown-up-controlled media
won't touch.

04:33.006 --> 04:36.999
- Plus I get to be on TV.
- Oh, honey. I'm so proud of you.

04:37.110 --> 04:41.046
All your hard work and grade-grubbing
have finally paid off.

04:41.147 --> 04:43.081
- So who's on your news team?
- [Gasps]

04:43.182 --> 04:45.616
Nerd. Nerd. Nelson?

04:45.718 --> 04:47.948
Well, we used to date.
Plus, he threatened me.

04:48.054 --> 04:49.954
Well, don't worry about sports.
I got that covered.

04:50.056 --> 04:52.684
Back off, Bart.
This may be the only chance I get...

04:52.792 --> 04:55.124
as a second-grader
to produce my own TV show...

04:55.228 --> 04:57.560
- and I'm not gonna let you screw it up.
- Mom.

04:57.664 --> 05:00.394
- Oh, let your brother do sports.
- Mom.

05:00.500 --> 05:03.697
That "Mom" stuff doesn't work on me.

05:05.938 --> 05:09.339
Ooh, the gum
with a cracker center.

05:09.442 --> 05:12.172
Mmm.
That'll do it, Apu.

05:12.278 --> 05:14.872
- So just-
- [Chittering]

05:14.981 --> 05:17.449
- [Shrieks]
- <i>[Apu] Do not be alarmed.</i>

05:17.550 --> 05:19.780
That is just my helper monkey, sir.

05:19.886 --> 05:22.286
I got him after a robber
shot me six times...

05:22.388 --> 05:24.754
and left me for dead.

05:24.857 --> 05:26.882
Helper monkey, eh?

05:26.993 --> 05:28.858
- [Chair Squeaking]
- [Chatter]

05:28.961 --> 05:31.020
[Laughter]

05:31.130 --> 05:33.655
Hey, I'm on TV.
Fart.

05:33.766 --> 05:36.064
Come on.
Quit fooling around, you guys.

05:37.403 --> 05:40.338
[Evil Voice]
So we meet again, Mr. Bond.

05:40.440 --> 05:43.932
- Bart, get out of my anchor chair.
- Silence, Octopussy.

05:44.043 --> 05:46.341
Come on.
This isn't a joke.

05:46.446 --> 05:50.473
All over town, kids are just waking up from
their naps cranky and hungry for the news.

05:51.584 --> 05:53.484
Wow. Kent Brockman.

05:53.586 --> 05:57.545
Good luck, kids.
Where the hell's my grilled cheese?

05:59.158 --> 06:02.059
- [Monkeys Chittering]
- I'd like a monkey, please.

06:02.161 --> 06:04.493
And maybe one of those dogs.
What do they do?

06:04.597 --> 06:07.361
Uh, they serve as seeing eyes
for the blind, sir.

06:07.467 --> 06:09.833
- Do they do any other tricks?
- No.

06:09.936 --> 06:12.632
- Just the monkey then.
- Uh, may I inquire...

06:12.739 --> 06:14.969
as to how you
are "differently-abled"?

06:15.074 --> 06:17.668
Oh. I'm not handicapped.

06:17.777 --> 06:20.109
I'm just lazy.

06:20.213 --> 06:24.274
Uh, sir, helper monkeys are only for
the physically-challenged or enfeebled.

06:24.384 --> 06:26.944
Enfeebled?
Ooh, I know just the guy.

06:27.053 --> 06:28.953
Be right back.

06:30.990 --> 06:32.890
- [Monkey Chittering]
- Oh, Son...

06:32.992 --> 06:35.927
this monkey's gonna change my life.

06:36.028 --> 06:37.996
Mind if I take him for a ride?

06:38.097 --> 06:39.997
Sure.
I'll just stand here.

06:40.099 --> 06:42.590
[Tires Squealing]

06:42.702 --> 06:45.899
Mmm, I can't wait
to eat that monkey.

06:46.005 --> 06:49.031
<i>##[Nelson Singing Intro Music]</i>

06:49.142 --> 06:51.542
And now, <i>Kidz Newz.</i>
## [Singing Melody]

06:51.644 --> 06:54.875
With <i>Kidz Newz</i> anchor- Lisa.
## [Singing Melody]

06:54.981 --> 06:57.814
Thank you.
Our top story today-

06:57.917 --> 07:00.351
In a move that could
affect children townwide...

07:00.453 --> 07:04.617
the library book purchase committee
slashed its budget by three percent.

07:04.724 --> 07:07.420
First on the chopping block-
periodicals.

07:07.527 --> 07:10.428
- Boring.
- And now sports.

07:10.530 --> 07:12.794
Bart Simpson telling you to lock
the doggy in the barn...

07:12.899 --> 07:15.891
'cause here comes dodgeball action.

07:16.002 --> 07:18.527
The shirts continued their domination
over the skins today.

07:18.638 --> 07:21.004
- And in school yard fights,
the highly anticipated match...
- [Bell Dings]

07:21.107 --> 07:24.736
between Kearney and Mr. Largo
ended in a disqualification...

07:24.844 --> 07:26.971
for use of dog-doo on a stick. Lisa.

07:28.381 --> 07:29.982
<i>[Nelson]</i>
<i>And we are out.</i>

07:29.982 --> 07:30.448
<i>[Nelson]</i>
<i>And we are out.</i>

07:36.689 --> 07:38.884
All right, kids.
We learned a lot today.

07:38.991 --> 07:41.323
Now this is what
makes my job difficult.

07:41.427 --> 07:43.190
- Bart, you're off the sports beat.
- What?

07:43.296 --> 07:45.890
Sorry, Bart, but you've gotta
take some things seriously.

07:45.998 --> 07:48.193
From now on,
you're Lisa's coanchor.

07:48.301 --> 07:49.825
- What?
- Ooh, that's gotta hurt.

07:49.936 --> 07:50.303
[Bell Dings]

07:50.303 --> 07:51.861
[Bell Dings]

07:52.004 --> 07:53.801
<i>[Bart]</i>
<i>Anchorman, huh?</i>

07:53.906 --> 07:56.431
Well, if I'm gonna be an anchorman,
I better go bleach the crud off my teeth.

07:56.542 --> 07:58.874
- I'll be in makeup.
- <i>[Door Closes]</i>

07:58.978 --> 08:01.378
I don't need a coanchor.
I'm a straight-A student.

08:01.481 --> 08:04.109
Lisa, Bart's got something
you can't learn in school-

08:04.217 --> 08:06.276
- "zazz."
- What is "zazz"?

08:06.385 --> 08:09.252
"Zing," "zork," "kapowza"-
Call it what you want.

08:09.355 --> 08:11.846
In any language
it spells mazuma in the bank.

08:11.958 --> 08:14.586
- "Zork"? What is "zork"?
- I didn't say "zork"?

08:14.694 --> 08:16.594
The point is the camera loves him.

08:16.696 --> 08:19.563
But that trivializes the whole idea
of <i>Kidz Newz.</i>

08:19.665 --> 08:21.292
I mean, let's be honest.

08:21.400 --> 08:23.561
Bart's not exactly the brightest penny
in the fountain.

08:23.669 --> 08:25.637
In English, Lisa.

08:25.738 --> 08:28.332
- [Motor Whirring]
- Damn blueberry stains.

08:28.441 --> 08:32.969
Look. I love Bart, but he's never even
read a newspaper.

08:33.078 --> 08:35.410
- [Motor Cuts Off]
- Between you and me, he's, well...

08:35.515 --> 08:37.414
kind of dumb.

08:37.517 --> 08:39.746
[Whimpers]

08:41.486 --> 08:43.955
- [Monkey Chittering]
- [Shouts]

08:45.358 --> 08:47.258
Is there a problem, honey?

08:47.360 --> 08:49.760
Monkey.
There's a monkey in the house.

08:49.862 --> 08:52.729
- [Yells]
- Relax. It's only Mojo.

08:52.832 --> 08:54.800
Mojo, Marge.
Marge, Mojo.

08:54.901 --> 08:57.028
He can do anything you show him.

08:57.136 --> 09:00.230
Watch.
Simpson residence.

09:02.475 --> 09:04.773
- [Chitters]
- [Sighs]

09:04.877 --> 09:08.369
Why didn't you tell me you were
bringing home a filthy monkey?

09:08.481 --> 09:12.474
This "filthy monkey" made the orange juice
you're drinking.

09:14.954 --> 09:17.514
I'll show Lisa who's dumb.

09:18.758 --> 09:20.692
"Supreme Court reverses"-

09:20.793 --> 09:23.261
[Groans]
I won't turn to the comics.

09:23.362 --> 09:25.387
I won't turn to the comics.

09:25.498 --> 09:28.194
All right. I'll read one comic
just to get me rollir.

09:28.301 --> 09:30.201
Archie.

09:30.303 --> 09:32.828
"Hey, Jughead, did you hear?
The Supreme Court reversed"-

09:32.939 --> 09:35.100
- [Groans]
- <i>[Marge Shouts]</i>

09:35.207 --> 09:37.198
<i>[Monkey Chittering]</i>

09:37.310 --> 09:39.505
- Mom, am I dumb?
- Honey, I'd love to reassure you...

09:39.612 --> 09:41.512
but right now Mommy needs
a tetanus shot.

09:44.150 --> 09:46.550
<i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>

09:46.652 --> 09:48.916
Mr. Brockman, I need your help.
I've got to become...

09:49.021 --> 09:51.148
a great anchor
so I can show up my sister.

09:51.257 --> 09:54.090
Sister, huh? [Chuckles]
I've got a sister.

09:54.193 --> 09:57.321
Miss Big Shot CNN
Washington Correspondent.

09:57.430 --> 09:58.590
[Scoffs]
Well, she's not the boss of me!

09:58.698 --> 09:59.231
Come in.

09:59.231 --> 09:59.458
Come in.

10:05.571 --> 10:07.232
Let's take the trophy route
to the den.

10:07.340 --> 10:09.808
Twelve Newsies.
Seven Iron Mikes.

10:09.909 --> 10:11.900
Four Golden Coifs.

10:12.011 --> 10:13.945
This is the most prestigious award
that Del Monte gives.

10:14.046 --> 10:16.378
Do you want to hear
my award-winning secret?

10:16.482 --> 10:19.144
Human interest stories.
They tug at the heart and fog the mind.

10:19.251 --> 10:21.310
Observe.

10:21.420 --> 10:23.183
Hear that?

10:23.289 --> 10:26.190
It's the sound
of childrers laughter...

10:26.292 --> 10:28.192
silenced.

10:28.294 --> 10:30.956
That's because tomorrow
this old carousel...

10:31.063 --> 10:34.260
which has delighted young Americans
for lo these past six years...

10:34.367 --> 10:37.928
will be torn down
to make way for the future-

10:38.037 --> 10:41.803
a store that sells
designer mouse pads.

10:41.907 --> 10:44.569
Well, I guess there's no room
in this modern world...

10:44.677 --> 10:47.168
for old Blackie here...

10:47.279 --> 10:49.179
but if you don't mind...

10:49.281 --> 10:51.374
this reporter is going for...

10:51.484 --> 10:53.645
one last ride.

10:53.753 --> 10:58.952
<i>##[Man Singing]</i>

10:59.058 --> 11:02.619
- This is Kent Brockman-
- <i>##[Continues]</i>

11:02.728 --> 11:04.628
reporting.

11:07.700 --> 11:09.793
## [Nelson Singing Melody]
And now...

11:09.902 --> 11:12.234
- <i>Kidz Newz.</i>
- [Groans]

11:12.338 --> 11:14.363
Marge, the kids are on.

11:14.473 --> 11:17.806
The monkey's on my part of the sofa.

11:17.910 --> 11:20.674
Honey, he's clearly
marked his territory.

11:20.780 --> 11:22.680
- [Groans]
- We'll bring you more...

11:22.782 --> 11:24.977
on this chalk shortage
as it continues.

11:25.084 --> 11:28.349
And now, Bart's been looking into
that alleged ham salad...

11:28.454 --> 11:30.388
from yesterday's school lunch.

11:30.489 --> 11:33.515
No, I haven't, Lisa.
Because I went out with a camera...

11:33.626 --> 11:35.594
and did a different kind of story.

11:35.695 --> 11:37.595
[Nervous Chuckles]
Bart, do you really think-

11:37.697 --> 11:40.359
It's about a man.
A simple man.

11:40.466 --> 11:43.697
He's one of... Bart's People.

11:45.237 --> 11:47.762
Joe Banks, 82 years young...

11:47.873 --> 11:49.773
has come to this pond every day...

11:49.875 --> 11:52.810
for the past 17 years
to feed the ducks.

11:52.912 --> 11:55.506
<i>But last month</i>
<i>Joe made a discovery-</i>

11:55.614 --> 11:58.481
<i>the ducks were gone.</i>

11:58.584 --> 12:01.075
Some say the ducks went to Canada.

12:01.187 --> 12:03.155
Others say Toronto.

12:03.255 --> 12:07.555
And some people think that
Joe used to sit down there, near those ducks.

12:07.660 --> 12:12.120
But it could be that there's just no room
in this modern world...

12:12.231 --> 12:15.962
for an old man and his ducks.

12:16.068 --> 12:19.196
<i>##[Man Singing]</i>

12:23.442 --> 12:25.603
Smithers-
[Sniffles]

12:25.711 --> 12:28.737
You think maybe my power plant
killed those ducks?

12:28.848 --> 12:31.248
There's no maybe about it, sir.

12:31.350 --> 12:33.250
[Sniffles]
Excellent.

12:33.352 --> 12:35.582
Marge, can I get a duck?

12:35.688 --> 12:38.122
You already have a monkey.

12:38.224 --> 12:40.124
Can he get a duck?

12:40.226 --> 12:42.387
- No!
- [Chittering]

12:44.697 --> 12:48.189
One man, no ducks.
Lisa.

12:48.300 --> 12:50.097
That's <i>Kidz Newz.</i>
Good night.

12:50.202 --> 12:52.102
- [Sobs]
- <i>[Applause]</i>

12:52.204 --> 12:54.536
Way to go, Bart.

12:56.008 --> 12:59.808
That wasrt news.
That was sappy, manipulative drivel.

12:59.912 --> 13:02.813
Well, I'm sorry you couldn't feel
for old Joe.

13:02.915 --> 13:06.851
- You didn't feel for him either, you big fat phony.
- <i>Bart, look up here.</i>

13:06.952 --> 13:10.319
This is where the tears would be if I could cry.
But I can't.

13:10.422 --> 13:13.289
Botched face-lift.
You could learn a lot from him, Maryann.

13:13.392 --> 13:15.451
- It's Lisa.
- Maryanrs better.

13:17.830 --> 13:20.697
They want cheap sentiment?
I'll pump 'em so full of sap...

13:20.800 --> 13:22.700
they'll be blowing their nose
with a pancake.

13:22.802 --> 13:25.396
They call her the "Cat Lady."

13:25.504 --> 13:29.998
People say she's crazy just because
she has a few dozen cats.

13:30.109 --> 13:34.307
But can anyone who loves animals that much
really be crazy?

13:34.413 --> 13:36.973
[Screaming Gibberish]

13:37.082 --> 13:38.982
[Cats Screeching]

13:40.386 --> 13:44.117
The old Union Pacific doesn't
come by here much anymore.

13:44.223 --> 13:46.623
<i>[Whistle Blowing]</i>

13:56.235 --> 13:59.204
- [Screaming Gibberish]
- [Cats Screeching]

14:05.644 --> 14:07.544
Come on.
Come to papa.

14:07.646 --> 14:09.375
[Monkey Chittering]

14:09.481 --> 14:11.506
Good boy, Mojo.
Now bring 'em down and I'll give you one.

14:14.587 --> 14:17.522
<i>[Groans]</i>
<i>Stop that. You're a helper monkey.</i>

14:17.623 --> 14:20.592
- This isn't helping.
- [Chitters]

14:22.194 --> 14:26.028
Oh. I don't need your pity.

14:26.131 --> 14:28.895
[Whimpering]

14:29.001 --> 14:30.901
[Chomping]

14:32.404 --> 14:35.032
<i>[Bart] Our forgotten veterans-</i>
<i>Their guns are quiet now.</i>

14:35.140 --> 14:37.040
<i>Their helmets lost or pawned.</i>

14:37.142 --> 14:41.772
And yet here they are,
making flags out of old clothes.

14:41.881 --> 14:45.647
Sure, they may not have
the right number of stripes...

14:45.751 --> 14:47.651
and the colors are all wrong...

14:47.753 --> 14:49.653
and some purists will tell you...

14:49.755 --> 14:53.748
the American flag doesn't contain
the word "Jordache."

14:53.859 --> 14:58.091
But you know, if they run this
up the flagpole, I'll salute.

14:58.197 --> 15:00.097
- I'm Bart Simpson.
- Hmm.

15:00.199 --> 15:03.134
Thank you, Bart, for yet another touching
Bart's People.

15:03.235 --> 15:07.194
- Now, turning to-
- I just think our veterans
deserve a little recognition.

15:07.306 --> 15:09.467
That's what Veterars Day is for, Bart.

15:09.575 --> 15:14.103
But is that really enough
to honor our brave soldiers?

15:14.213 --> 15:17.114
[Nervous Chuckle]
They also have Memorial Day.

15:17.216 --> 15:19.480
Oh, Lisa. Maybe you're right,
maybe you're wrong.

15:19.585 --> 15:21.485
The important thing
is veterans deserve a day...

15:21.587 --> 15:23.817
- to honor them.
- They have two.

15:23.923 --> 15:26.551
Well, maybe they should have three.
I'm Bart Simpson.

15:29.695 --> 15:32.061
Oh, my.
Look at all these letters from people...

15:32.164 --> 15:34.064
who want to be Bart's people, Bart.

15:34.166 --> 15:38.796
I wish they could all be Bart's people, Mom.
I truly do.

15:38.904 --> 15:40.895
I'm proud of you, honey.

15:41.006 --> 15:43.304
You're finally giving something
back to the community...

15:43.409 --> 15:46.845
after taking so, so much.

15:46.946 --> 15:49.847
Hmm.
Really makes you think.

15:49.949 --> 15:51.849
What does that even mean?

15:51.951 --> 15:54.181
Mom might not
see through you, but I do.

15:54.286 --> 15:56.186
You don't care about
any of these people.

15:56.288 --> 16:00.054
Well, If I'm guilty of anything,
maybe it's caring too much.

16:00.159 --> 16:03.060
- I'm Bart Simpson.
- Stop talking like that. Stop it.

16:03.162 --> 16:05.062
- [Choking]
- Lisa, please.

16:05.164 --> 16:07.223
You've absolutely no reason
to be jealous.

16:07.333 --> 16:10.461
You're still a very important part
of Bart's show.

16:10.569 --> 16:12.799
[Groans]

16:15.774 --> 16:18.675
Bart's show? If everybody knew
what a phony Bart was...

16:18.777 --> 16:21.075
he'd be off that show so fast-

16:21.180 --> 16:23.671
I've got it.
[Laughter]

16:26.485 --> 16:28.783
[Monkey Mimics Laughter]

16:28.887 --> 16:30.787
[Yells]

16:35.794 --> 16:38.729
Hey, Lise.
Be a doll and hand me that sealant.

16:41.333 --> 16:44.734
Hey. Here's another letter
for Bart's People.

16:44.837 --> 16:48.273
Oh. So many souls, so little ain'time.

16:48.374 --> 16:50.865
- [Motor Hums]
- " Dear Bart...

16:50.976 --> 16:54.309
"I came to this country
hoping to share the American dream.

16:54.413 --> 16:56.813
"But after many years
of backbreaking labor...

16:56.915 --> 16:59.406
I find myself homeless
and sleeping in a junkyard."

16:59.518 --> 17:01.782
Oh, how terrible.
Read on.

17:01.887 --> 17:05.185
"Should I abandon hope or fight on bravely
against impossible odds?"

17:05.290 --> 17:07.190
Oh, this is too perfect.

17:07.291 --> 17:11.353
- It is, isn't it?
- I'm gonna put him on the air tonight. Live.

17:11.463 --> 17:15.160
Oh, Bart, you'll have to ride your bike
pretty fast to get out there in time.

17:15.267 --> 17:18.236
- Nah, I'll just take the chopper.
- They gave you a chopper?

17:21.040 --> 17:22.940
[Wheezing]

17:23.041 --> 17:26.603
- Mojo, will you wipe my mouth?
- [Chitters]

17:26.712 --> 17:31.115
Oh, for Pete sakes,
why is that monkey wearing a diaper?

17:31.216 --> 17:33.946
- I thought he was housebroken?
- [Both] Meh.

17:34.053 --> 17:36.385
[Groans]

17:36.488 --> 17:40.254
You said this monkey would be
sweeping the floors and cleaning the gutters...

17:40.359 --> 17:44.352
and now he just lies there
struggling to breathe.

17:44.463 --> 17:46.693
- [Labored Breathing]
- <i>[Homer] What do you want?</i>

17:46.799 --> 17:49.131
His cholesterol's through the roof.

17:49.234 --> 17:51.134
I want you to take
that monkey back...

17:51.236 --> 17:54.694
so he can be rehabilitated
and get a second chance.

17:54.807 --> 17:57.037
No, no.
He's fine.

17:57.142 --> 17:59.770
Go on, Mojo.
Show Marge your happy dance.

17:59.878 --> 18:02.608
[Groaning]

18:02.714 --> 18:05.979
[Lethargic Chittering]

18:07.086 --> 18:09.646
- And so on.
- [Groans]

18:09.755 --> 18:12.121
- <i>[Door Opens]</i>
- <i>[Footsteps]</i>

18:12.224 --> 18:14.124
[Door Buzzing]

18:14.226 --> 18:16.319
- <i>[Door Closes]</i>
- <i>[Tires Squealing]</i>

18:16.428 --> 18:19.920
[Gasps]
Mojo. What have they done to you?

18:23.135 --> 18:26.627
[Computerized Voice]
Pray for Mojo.

18:26.738 --> 18:31.539
So, by waking up a little early
and having some extra sheets handy...

18:31.643 --> 18:33.770
no one's the wiser.

18:33.879 --> 18:36.313
Tomorrow- destroying the evidence.

18:36.415 --> 18:39.873
Ew. Uh, thank you, Milhouse.

18:39.985 --> 18:44.149
Now it's time for today's special live edition
of Bart's People.

18:44.256 --> 18:49.125
[Clears Throat]
Lisa, I've just arrived at the Springfield dump.

18:49.228 --> 18:51.128
A lot of things get thrown out here.

18:51.230 --> 18:54.631
Sometimes even a human being.

18:54.733 --> 18:56.963
Somewhere in this pile
of twisted metal...

18:57.069 --> 18:59.060
and soiled mattresses-

18:59.171 --> 19:01.662
- [Nervous Chuckles]
- lives a poor immigrant...

19:01.773 --> 19:04.867
whose home was cruelly taken away.

19:04.977 --> 19:06.877
Yeah. By you!

19:06.979 --> 19:09.379
Groundskeeper Willie!
Um, uh...

19:09.481 --> 19:12.109
so you're the immigrant
I'm here to help.

19:12.217 --> 19:14.685
Help?
You destroyed my house...

19:14.786 --> 19:17.584
and reduced me to livir in a dump.

19:17.689 --> 19:19.850
Groundskeeper Willie, furious with
the government that let him down.

19:19.958 --> 19:21.892
- I'm Bart Simp-
- <i>[Screams]</i>

19:21.994 --> 19:24.963
- [Laughs]
- I'll kill ya!

19:25.063 --> 19:26.963
- [Grunts]
- [Screams]

19:27.065 --> 19:28.965
- [Crash, Audio Cuts Out]
- Oh, no.

19:29.067 --> 19:31.934
What have I done?
Nelson, cover for me.

19:37.276 --> 19:39.176
[Clears Throat]

19:39.278 --> 19:41.838
[Imitating Farts]

19:47.019 --> 19:50.887
Oh, Bart. It's me,
a jolly policeman.

19:50.989 --> 19:55.289
Oh, we got Willie. Come on out
so we can give you a medal.

19:55.394 --> 19:57.294
Way to go, Officer.
[Screams]

19:57.396 --> 19:59.694
- [Groans]
- [Yelps]

19:59.798 --> 20:01.527
- [Grunts]
- <i>[Yelps]</i>

20:01.633 --> 20:04.124
- Willie, stop!
- Away with ya.

20:04.236 --> 20:07.672
I got to finish him off
while I'm still temporarily insane!

20:07.773 --> 20:10.571
No, you can't hurt Bart!

20:10.676 --> 20:12.906
He's-Well, he's your son.

20:13.011 --> 20:16.378
- What?
- Well, not literally.

20:16.481 --> 20:19.848
But in a way,
isn't he everyone's son?

20:19.952 --> 20:22.443
For you see,
that little hell-raiser...

20:22.554 --> 20:25.250
is the spawn of every
shrieking commercial...

20:25.357 --> 20:27.587
every brain-rotting soda pop...

20:27.693 --> 20:30.127
every teacher who cares
less about young minds...

20:30.229 --> 20:33.255
than about cashing
their big fat paychecks.

20:33.365 --> 20:35.833
No, Bart's not to blame.

20:35.934 --> 20:40.200
You can't create a monster and then whine
when he stomps on a few buildings.

20:40.305 --> 20:43.934
- I'm Lisa Simpson.
- [Sniffles, Sobs]

20:45.477 --> 20:48.469
You're right.
It's all Willie's fault.

20:48.580 --> 20:51.208
I've been a terrible father.

20:51.316 --> 20:53.216
Hey, Lise. Thanks.

20:53.318 --> 20:56.378
Boy, that phony schmaltz
of yours sure is powerful stuff.

20:56.488 --> 20:59.082
Uh, yeah. But I have
a certain respect...

20:59.191 --> 21:01.659
for that whole "truth and hard work" thing
that you do.

21:01.760 --> 21:06.026
You know, Bart, if we combine
your showmanship with my integrity...

21:06.131 --> 21:08.565
we could make kids
really care about the news.

21:08.667 --> 21:12.728
You're right. If we work together,
there's no stoppir us.

21:14.239 --> 21:16.901
